<subSubSection pageId="39" pageNumber="433" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="39.[728,1319,1085,1504]" pageId="39" pageNumber="433">
<taxonomicName box="[733,974,1273,1306]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Cryptotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="39" pageNumber="433" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="soricinus">Cryptotis soricinus</taxonomicName>
traditionally has been considered a subspecies of C. parvus but is now recognized as a distinct species in the C. parvus group, somewhat tentatively, based primarily on limited morphological data. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[115,874,1515,1544]" pageId="39" pageNumber="433" type="distribution">
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6871102" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6871102" box="[115,874,1515,1544]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6871102/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="433" targetBox="[114,705,1086,1502]" targetPageId="39">
<paragraph blockId="39.[115,1321,1515,2489]" box="[115,874,1515,1544]" pageId="39" pageNumber="433">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[115,291,1515,1544]" pageId="39" pageNumber="433">Distribution.</emphasis>
